The paper deals with randomized algorithms for combinatorial problems, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The problems studied in the paper involve paths and packings, which are also relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
